TEED – Business Logic & System Flow Documentation (v1)
1. CORE TRUTH (Read this or TEED fails)

TEED is NOT:

a website

a dashboard

an AI chatbot

a PWA

TEED IS:

A multi-tenant business operating system for digital entrepreneurs.

If your logic doesn’t treat TEED as a business OS, you’re building trash.

2. CORE ENTITIES (Non-Negotiable)
2.1 User

A human being.

Key rules

A User can own multiple Businesses

A User can belong to multiple Businesses

A User has one identity, many contexts

2.2 Business (Tenant)

This is the real customer, not the user.

Key rules

Everything in TEED belongs to a Business

Data NEVER crosses businesses

Business switching is mandatory (no shortcuts)

2.3 Membership

Connects User ↔ Business

Roles

Owner (full control)

Admin

Staff

Viewer

Key rules

Permissions come from Membership, not User

One User = different role per Business

3. HIGH-LEVEL SYSTEM FLOW
3.1 Authentication Flow

User logs in

System fetches:

All Businesses user belongs to

If:

0 businesses → onboarding

1 business → auto-select

1 → force business switch screen

active_business stored in session / token

⚠️ If active business is missing → API MUST FAIL

3.2 Business Context Enforcement (CRITICAL)

Every request must answer:

“Which business is this for?”

If not → 403 Forbidden

This is where most startups screw up.

4. TEED MODULE ARCHITECTURE

Each module follows the same pattern:

Business
 └── Module
     ├── Data
     ├── Analytics
     ├── AI Layer
     └── Actions


No exceptions.

5. CORE MODULES & LOGIC FLOW
5.1 Business Onboarding Module
Flow

User creates Business

System:

Creates Business record

Assigns user as Owner

Initializes default modules

Business becomes selectable

Business Rules

Business name must be unique per owner

Currency, country, timezone locked after creation (v1)

5.2 Social Presence Module
Purpose

Help businesses grow visibility (Instagram, Facebook, Google).

Logic Flow

Business connects social account

System stores:

platform

account_id

access scope

Data pulled on schedule

Metrics stored per business

Metrics

followers

reach

engagement

post frequency

AI Usage

Caption suggestions

Bio optimization

Posting time analysis

⚠️ AI suggests, never auto-posts (trust issue).

5.3 Ads & Growth Module (Meta Focus)
Flow

Business links ad account

System:

pulls ad status

detects errors / limitations

AI explains issues in human language

Core Logic

Raw API error → AI explanation → action checklist

No magic promises.
If you promise “fix bans automatically”, that’s bullshit.

5.4 Smart Payments / Escrow Module
Purpose

Trust layer between buyer & seller.

Flow

Order created

Payment collected

Funds held (pending)

Trigger events:

delivery confirmed

dispute opened

Funds released or reversed

Business Rules

TEED never owns funds

TEED only orchestrates

Full audit trail required

5.5 Analytics Engine (Central Nervous System)
Data Sources

Sales

Social

Ads

Customer behavior

Logic

Raw events → normalized metrics

Time windows:

daily

weekly

monthly

yearly

Output

KPIs

Trends

Comparisons

⚠️ Analytics must be read-only to users.

5.6 AI Partner Layer (Non-Optional)

AI is not a chatbot.

AI Inputs

Business context

Module data

User intent

AI Outputs

Explanations

Suggestions

Risk warnings

Roadmaps

Hard Rule

AI NEVER:

executes payments

changes data

bypasses permissions

AI is an advisor, not an admin.

6. API LOGIC (Conceptual, No Code)
API Design Rules

Every endpoint requires:

authenticated user

active business

Business ID inferred, not passed manually

Permission checked via Membership

Example Endpoint Categories
Auth

login

logout

refresh

Business

create

switch

settings

members

Modules

/social/*

/ads/*

/payments/*

/analytics/*

7. SERIALIZER RESPONSIBILITIES (Conceptual)

Serializers are gatekeepers, not data dumpers.

Responsibilities

Validate ownership

Enforce business scope

Shape API output

Hide sensitive fields

Rule

If a serializer doesn’t know the business, it’s invalid.

8. SIGNALS & EVENTS (SYSTEM BRAIN)

Signals are domain events, not hacks.

Core Events

user_joined_business

business_created

payment_completed

dispute_opened

analytics_snapshot_created

Signal Rules

No business logic in views

Signals trigger:

notifications

analytics updates

AI insights refresh

9. PERMISSION MODEL (BRUTALLY SIMPLE)
Role	Access Level
Owner	Everything
Admin	Manage modules & staff
Staff	Operate assigned modules
Viewer	Read-only

No custom permissions in v1.
Custom perms early = design suicide.

10. FAILURE POINTS (READ CAREFULLY)

If you do these, TEED will fail:

❌ Business ID in URLs everywhere
❌ AI making promises it can’t keep
❌ No strict tenant isolation
❌ Overengineering permissions
❌ Building UI before locking logic

11. REALITY CHECK (No Sugarcoating)

This scope is huge

MVP must ship with:

Business

Membership

One strong module (Analytics OR Ads)

Everything else is staged

Trying to ship all modules at once = guaranteed collapse

